PUB_PUB_FORMATTED: Montfort, P.D. de 1810. Conchyliologie Systematique, et Classification Methodique des Coquilles. Paris : F. Schoell Tome 2 676 + 16 pp.

QUALIFICATION: the name Ricinula appeared in the heading of plate 395, which depicts 7 different species, none of which is named. Lamarck [1822, Histoire naturelle des animaux sans vertèbres, 7: 230-233] named these 7 species, and two additional ones, in Ricinula. Gray, 1847, Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 15: 139, designated Murex neritoideus, and Cossmann, 1903, Essais de paléoconchologie comparée, 5: 79, designated Murex ricinus Linnaeus as type species of Ricinula. Neither Murex neritoideus nor Murex ricinus were originally included species. Ricinulus [Desmarest, 1858, in Chenu, Encyclopédie d'histoire naturelle, Crustacés, Mollusques, Zoophytes: 174] is an incorrect subsequent spelling; = morum Röding

Rapanus Sowerby [non Schumacher, 1817] 1839 is listed as a separate name in Neave, 1940, Nomenclator Zoologicus, 4: 12, but Sowerby [A conchological manual, ed. 1: 92] explicitly attributed the name to Schumacher. Prior to Radwin & d'Attilio, Cossmann [1903, Essais de paléoconchologie comparée, 5: 63] and Wenz [1941, Handbuch der Paläozoologie, 6(5): 1083] cited Buccinum bezoar Linnaeus, 1767, as the type species; however, although it is a senior subjective synonym of Rapana foliacea, it was not an originally included nominal species, and this did not qualify as a valid type designation
